Source: tlsv1-scan
Section: net
Priority: optional
Maintainer: Gratien D'haese <gratien.dhaese@gmail.com>
Build-Depends: debhelper-compat (= 13), gcc, make
Standards-Version: 4.6.0
Homepage: https://github.com/gdha/TLSv1-scan

Package: tlsv1-scan
Architecture: any
Depends: ${shlibs:Depends}, ${misc:Depends}, sslscan, iproute2, lsof, net-tools
Description: Scan local system for services using deprecated TLSv1.0 or TLSv1.1
 TLSv1-scan scans all local TCP listening ports and checks each one for
 TLSv1.0 or TLSv1.1 support using sslscan, then reports the owning process
 for any service where those deprecated protocol versions are enabled.
